President Biden spoke with President Zelenskyy of Ukraine and expressed concerns about Russia's aggressive actions towards Ukraine. He reassured Ukraine of the United States' commitment to its sovereignty and territorial integrity. President Biden emphasized that any decisions or discussions about Ukraine must involve Ukraine. Both leaders called for Russia to de-escalate tensions and agreed that diplomacy is the best approach for resolving the conflict. President Biden also highlighted the United States' willingness to support confidence-building measures to implement the Minsk Agreements.